---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="DoItSwift Roadmap | DoItSwift"
  description="What we're thinking about building next at DoItSwift — exploratory plans, not a store. Core tools stay free; share feedback on the contact page."
  keywords="doitswift roadmap, future plans, what's coming"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="roadmap-note">Shaping what we build next — share your ideas</p>
      <h1>What's coming</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Today, every DoItSwift tool is free and runs in your browser — no account required. The notes below are
        exploratory: we're sketching possible directions, including ideas for optional deeper workflows (batch flows,
        presets, support) for people who want them. This is not a product page or a promise to ship or charge for
        anything specific.
      </p>

      <h2>What stays free</h2>
      <p>
        Core conversion, compression, resizing, and encoding features you use today are intended to remain available
        without a subscription. If we ever add optional extras, the aim is not to lock everyday basics behind a
        paywall.
      </p>

      <h2>Ideas under consideration</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Advanced batch and automation options</li>
        <li>Preset packs and reusable settings</li>
        <li>Priority support and early access to new tools</li>
        <li>Additional export and workflow integrations over time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Details and pricing would only be shared when and if we're ready — and nothing changes for casual users who are
        happy with the free tools.
      </p>

      <h2>Have input?</h2>
      <p>
        If there's something you'd like to see — or something you want to stay free forever — tell us on the{' '}
        <a href="/contact/" class="link-back">contact page</a>. It genuinely shapes what we build next.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/" class="link-back">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .roadmap-note {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
